A bar attendant has been fined Sh30,000 for stealing from her employer.  On Thursday, Pamela Wanja, convicted on her own plea of guilt, will serve five months in prison if she fails to pay the fine.  She was accused of stealing Sh16,100 from her employer Judith Ndegi on May 3, 2021, at Kiamanyeki market in Mwea East.  Principal Magistrate Miriam Mugure observed that the accused took the cash after closing the bar before she was arrested from her hideout.  She said Ms Wanja committed a serious crime and should be punished to discourage her from repeating the same.  Making bar maids’ job professional  Making bar maids’ job professional In mitigation, Ms Wanja admitted to having stolen the cash but asked for leniency from the court. She told the court that she was an orphan and that she was struggling to survive.    Take a quick survey and help us improve our website! By Fidelis Kabunyi | 11 hours ago By Fidelis Kabunyi | 2 days ago By Gitau Wanyoike | 2 days ago By James Munyeki | 2 days ago Southern Bypass crash victim identified